exportmetadata: The "3 3682-Ascalon sandy loam, 3 to 9 percent slopes" mapunit was combined with the "3 2tlny-Ascalon sandy loam, 3 to 9 percent slopes" map unit as a result of the " SDJR - MLRA 67B - Ascalon sandy loam/fine sandy loam, 3-9% slopes " project, in the Soil Data Join Recorrelation Initiative (SDJR). The tabular database was edited and populated according to guidance in National Instruction (NI-305) exhibits A and B. The "30 3683-Fort Collins loam, 0 to 3 percent slopes" mapunit was combined with the "118 2rgqs-Fort loam, 1 to 5 percent slopes, cool" map unit as a result of the " SDJR MLRA 69C Fort Collins map units " project, in the Soil Data Join Recorrelation Initiative (SDJR). The tabular database was edited and populated according to guidance in National Instruction (NI-305) exhibits A and B. The "31 3684-Fort Collins loam, 3 to 8 percent slopes" mapunit was combined with the "118 2rgqs-Fort loam, 1 to 5 percent slopes, cool" map unit as a result of the " SDJR MLRA 69C Fort Collins map units " project, in the Soil Data Join Recorrelation Initiative (SDJR). The tabular database was edited and populated according to guidance in National Instruction (NI-305) exhibits A and B. The "51 368v-Manzanola clay loam, 0 to 1 percent slopes" mapunit was combined with the "52 2w4nr-Manzanst clay loam, 0 to 3 percent slopes" map unit as a result of the " SDJR MLRA 67B Manzanst map units " project, in the Soil Data Join Recorrelation Initiative (SDJR). The tabular database was edited and populated according to guidance in National Instruction (NI-305) exhibits A and B. The "52 368w-Manzanola clay loam, 1 to 3 percent slopes" mapunit was combined with the "52 2w4nr-Manzanst clay loam, 0 to 3 percent slopes" map unit as a result of the " SDJR MLRA 67B Manzanst map units " project, in the Soil Data Join Recorrelation Initiative (SDJR).
